<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-9887] failed-task-count JMX metric not updated if task fails during startup</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-9887</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If a task fails on startup (specifically, during &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/00a59b392d92b0d6d3a321ef9a53dae4b3a9d030/connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/Worker.java#L427-L468&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;this code section&lt;/a&gt;), the &lt;tt&gt;failed-task-count&lt;/tt&gt; JMX metric is not updated to reflect the task failure, even though the status endpoints in the REST API do report the task as failed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13299189">KAFKA-9887</key>
            <summary>failed-task-count JMX metric not updated if task fails during startup</summary>
